#: ../../content/news/2025-08-03_02.06.00.md:1
msgid "2.6 (2025-08-03)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2025-08-03_02.06.00.md:3
msgid "Adjustments to local-sources interaction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2025-08-03_02.06.00.md:5
msgid ""
"Two adjustments have been made for user's who utilize local-sources mode. "
"First, when running releng-tool configured for a local-sources mode, paths "
"of any configured local-source overrides are now always printed at the start"
" of a releng-tool run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2025-08-03_02.06.00.md:10
msgid ""
"The second improvement is the handling of provided local-sources paths on "
"the command line. Supported paths would include explicit directories; "
"however, if a trailing slash was provided in the path, the mapping to the "
"package may not work. This is not ideal for users utilizing path expansion "
"in their shells which typically end in trailing slashes. releng-tool has "
"been updated to now accept trailing-slashed paths."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2025-08-03_02.06.00.md:17
msgid "Rework of provided staging/target/host paths for CMake projects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2025-08-03_02.06.00.md:19
msgid ""
"CMake-based projects are provided locations for various include, library and"
" module paths in their configuration stages. This is to help hint at assets "
"generated by packages that can be found by other packages that locally "
"depend on them. However, some limitations have existed in how releng-tool "
"configured a project, especially for environments which used strict "
"`CMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH_MODE_*` modes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2025-08-03_02.06.00.md:26
msgid ""
"While projects are invoked with [`CMAKE_INCLUDE_PATH`][cmake-include-path], "
"[`CMAKE_LIBRARY_PATH`][cmake-library-path], etc. to help find various "
"resources; a [`CMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH`][cmake-find-root-path] path was never "
"provided. This could be problematic for builds that may be configured with, "
"for example, [`CMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH_MODE_INCLUDE`][cmake-find-root-path-"
"mode-include] set to `ONLY` and options like `CMAKE_INCLUDE_PATH` are "
"ignored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2025-08-03_02.06.00.md:33
msgid ""
"Toolchain configurations should be configuring [`CMAKE_SYSROOT`][cmake-"
"sysroot] and ideally allow `CMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH` to be tailored (if a "
"caller can provide extended sysroot paths). Since releng-tool now provides "
"`CMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH`, toolchain configurations should be able to support "
"the base toolchain sysroot and additional staged/target files prepared by a "
"releng-tool project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2025-08-03_02.06.00.md:39
msgid "Example toolchain configuration should ideally support either:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2025-08-03_02.06.00.md:45
msgid "Or:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2025-08-03_02.06.00.md:53
msgid ""
"Before the use of `CMAKE_FIND_ROOT_PATH`, releng-tool used to configure "
"[`CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH`][cmake-prefix-path] to help projects find content in "
"the staging/target area. This resulted in some undesired side effects as it "
"could result in program finding to try to find/use staged/target executables"
" in the host environment. Defining the prefix path is not required with the "
"proper find-related configurations; therefore, releng-tool will no longer "
"explicitly configure `CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH`."
msgstr ""

